.SH "NAME"
MooseX::Daemonize::WithPidFile \- A Role with the core daemonization and pidfile management
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.22
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&  package My::Daemon;
\&  use Moose;
\&
\&  with \*(AqMooseX::Daemonize::WithPidFile\*(Aq;
\&
\&  sub start {
\&      my $self = shift;
\&      # daemonize me ...
\&      $self\->daemonize; # << this will write the pidfile for you
\&      # return from the parent,...
\&      return unless $self\->is_daemon;
\&      # but continue on in the child (daemon)
\&  }
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a slightly extended basic daemonization Role, it provides
Pidfile management along with the core daemonization features
found in MooseX::Daemonize::Core.
.SH "ATTRIBUTES"
.IX Header "ATTRIBUTES"
.IP "\fIpidfile (is =\fR rw, isa => MooseX::Daemonize::Pid::File)>" 4
.IX Item "pidfile (is = rw, isa => MooseX::Daemonize::Pid::File)>"
This attribute holds the MooseX::Daemonize::Pid::File object used
to manage the Pidfile. It will initialize the object using the
\&\f(CW\*(C`init_pidfile\*(C'\fR method (which is required by this role).
.SH "REQUIRED METHODS"
.IX Header "REQUIRED METHODS"
.IP "\fIinit_pidfile\fR" 4
.IX Item "init_pidfile"
This method is used to build the \fIpidfile\fR attribute's object. It should
return a MooseX::Daemonize::Pid::File object.
.IP "\fBhas_pidfile\fR" 4
.IX Item "has_pidfile"
This is a predicate method to tell you if your \fIpidfile\fR attribute has
been initialized yet.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
.IP "\fBdaemonize\fR" 4
.IX Item "daemonize"
This adds an \f(CW\*(C`after\*(C'\fR method modifier to the \f(CW\*(C`daemonize\*(C'\fR method (from
MooseX::Daemonize::Core) and handles writing your Pidfile for you.
.IP "\fBmeta\fR" 4
.IX Item "meta"
The \f(CW\*(C`meta()\*(C'\fR method from Class::MOP::Class
